  "prompt": "Where can I rent a big apartment in Seattle and not pay too much money?",
  "response": "Finding a large apartment in Seattle at an affordable price can be challenging due to the city's high cost of living. However, here are some tips and areas to consider:\n\n### Areas to Consider:\n1. **North Seattle**: Neighborhoods like Northgate, Lake City, and Bitter Lake might offer more affordable rental options compared to areas closer to downtown.\n   \n2. **West Seattle**: While some parts can be pricey, neighborhoods like Arbor Heights and South Delridge might have relatively better deals.\n\n3. **South Seattle**: Areas such as Rainier Valley or South Lake Union can be more affordable, especially if you're willing to sacrifice some proximity to amenities.\n\n4. **Beacon Hill**: This neighborhood is often more affordable compared to Capitol Hill and has good access to transit.\n\n5. **White Center and Burien**: Just outside of Seattle, these areas can offer larger units for less money while still being a reasonable commute to the city.\n\n### Tips for Finding Affordable Rentals:\n- **Search Online**: Utilize websites like Craigslist, Zillow, Apartments.com, or Rent.com to browse current listings.\n- **Consider Shared Housing**: If you're open to sharing, look for roommate situations which can drastically reduce cost.\n- **Off-Peak Season**: Rental prices can fluctuate seasonally; looking during off-peak months (like winter) may yield better deals.\n- **Negotiate**: In some cases, landlords may be willing to negotiate rent, especially if you can sign a longer lease.\n- **Check Local Listings**: Often, smaller landlords may list their properties on local bulletin boards or community boards.\n  \n### Additional Resources:\n- **Social Media Groups**: Look for local Facebook groups dedicated to Seattle housing; members often post listings or sublets.\n- **Housing Assistance Programs**: Research organizations that offer resources for finding affordable housing options.\n\nAlways remember to inspect the apartment and review the lease agreements carefully before committing. Good luck with your search!",
